            "version": "1.1.4",
            "released": "2026-06-19",
            "notes": "`<deck-stat-grid cols=\"6\">` \u2014 six-up headline number row. CSS rule. added as peer of cols 2-5; docstring bumped from `2 | 3 | 4 | 5` to `2 | 3 | 4 | 5 | 6` with a canvas-width ceiling note (6 fits a 1040 canvas; 7+ start to clip values like `1.2M`). Earned during the Phase 2 step-5 trial \u2014 the `how-i-use-ai` source deck uses 6-up stat rows on its scale slide. Folded into `kitchen-sink.html` as the regression surface.",
            "paths": {
                "css": "slide-decks/1.1.4/deck.css",
                "js": "slide-decks/1.1.4/deck.js"
            },
            "floats": []
        },
        {
            "version": "1.1.3",
            "released": "2026-06-19",
            "notes": "`<deck-stat>` border now follows `--accent-color` (falling back to. `--border`), so `tone=\u2026` fully tints the tile rather than only the value text. Retires the per-tile inline border hack from the architectural-approaches migration. `<deck-slide nav-hide>` per-slide opt-out: slide is omitted from the. auto-built top rail (still navigable via keyboard / direct hash). `<deck-config nav=\"auto|chapters|all\">`. `auto` (the new default). shows every slide on the top bar when total \u2264 5; once a deck is longer than 5 slides it switches to chapters-only (slides with `variant=\"chapter\"`, plus the title slide and any `variant=\"discuss\"`). `chapters` forces chapters-only regardless of count; `all` keeps the pre-1.1.3 every-slide behaviour. The prior `nav=\"default\"` is effectively `nav=\"auto\"`. `<deck-mark>` documented as the cell-pill primitive for plain. `<table class=\"compare-table\">` 3-col comparisons (README + the `deck-compare.js` docstring carry the recipe; no new element). New `decks/templates/starter.html` (minimal) and. `decks/templates/kitchen-sink.html` (9-slide reference) \u2014 the kitchen-sink doubles as the regression surface for all four library changes above.",
            "paths": {
                "css": "slide-decks/1.1.3/deck.css",
                "js": "slide-decks/1.1.3/deck.js"
            },
            "floats": []
        },
        {
            "version": "1.1.2",
            "released": "2026-06-19",
            "notes": "`bin/deck-build dist` now generates `manifest.json` and embeds a. `claude-utils@<sha>` stamp at the top of `deck.{css,js}`. `bin/deck-build docs` regenerates `components.md` and the README. cheat-sheet from `@element` headers in `elements/*.js` \u2014 no more hand-editing the table. Frozen-pin guard refuses to overwrite a published exact-pin path. with non-identical bytes; monotonicity check refuses VERSION lower than any published; intra-day theme collision check refuses to rewrite a same-day theme snapshot with different bytes. All three bypassed by `--force-republish`. Pre-hydrate fallback CSS extended to cover child element hosts. (deck-card-title, deck-flow-sub, deck-stat-value, etc.). Tone vocabulary reconciled across `deck-callout`, `deck-mark`,. `deck-badge`, `deck-tag`: every tone-accepting element now accepts the canonical six (`success | info | highlight | warning | muted | danger`); `deck-callout`'s `note` retained as a legacy alias. Hover host-resolution: `setupHover()` now walks up via `.closest()`. against an explicit host-class list, so the indicator lands on the outer host (e.g. `deck-step-row`) rather than the inner body wrapper.",
            "paths": {
                "css": "slide-decks/1.1.2/deck.css",
                "js": "slide-decks/1.1.2/deck.js"
            },
            "floats": []
